+# Tribe Studio — content production pipeline
+
+Solo short-form-video creator workflow: Vault (ideas) → Pipeline (5 stages: Brainstorm → Pre-production → Production → Post-production → Publish) → Done. Pure client-side React SPA (Vite + React 18 + React Router v7), localStorage-backed, no backend, no env vars.
+
+## Branch policy
+
+- Active development: `restructuring-saas-design`
+- Do **not** merge to `main` — main has 96 commits of unrelated F1/F2 multi-workspace + social-account work that built on top of screens this branch deleted. Merging would either lose F1/F2 or kill the new pipeline. Both branches stay separate for now.
+
+## Deploy to homelab → `tribe.learnmeld.com`
+
+The current branch is live at https://tribe.learnmeld.com (HTTP basic auth gated) on the user's homelab VPS as a homelab "product". Static SPA served by `nginx:alpine` behind Caddy. Cloudflare DNS → VPS eth0 → Caddy → nginx → built `dist/`.
+
+### Ship a new build
+
+```bash
+npm run deploy
+```
+
+Builds `dist/` and rsyncs it to `homelab:/opt/homelab/products/tribe/html/`. No container restart needed — nginx serves files live from the bind mount. Cache headers: `index.html` is `no-cache`, `/assets/*` is content-hashed + `immutable` (1yr), so deploys reflect on the next page load.
+
+Run this after any UI change worth showing the friend.
+
+### Where things live
+
+| | |
+|---|---|
+| Live URL | `https://tribe.learnmeld.com` (basic auth: user `tribe`) |
+| Local build origin | `dist/` from `npm run build` |
+| VPS path | `/opt/homelab/products/tribe/` |
+| SPA files served from | `/opt/homelab/products/tribe/html/` (bind-mounted into nginx) |
+| Caddy snippet | `/opt/homelab/products/tribe/caddy.snippet` (basic_auth + reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8600) |
+| nginx config | `/opt/homelab/products/tribe/nginx.conf` (SPA `try_files` fallback) |
+| TLS cert | Caddy DNS-01 via Cloudflare token in `homelab:/opt/homelab/core/.env` |
+| DNS | Cloudflare A record `tribe.learnmeld.com → 37.27.67.15` (proxied) |
+
+### Rotate the basic-auth password
+
+```bash
+ssh homelab "docker run --rm caddy:2 caddy hash-password --plaintext 'new-pass'"
+# Paste new hash into /opt/homelab/products/tribe/caddy.snippet basic_auth block
+ssh homelab "cd /opt/homelab/products/tribe && sudo just _sync-caddy"
+```
+
+The credential is bound to the user `tribe`; share new password with friend out-of-band (Signal/Telegram), never in chat history or commits.
+
+### Operate on the VPS
+
+```bash
+ssh homelab
+cd /opt/homelab/products/tribe
+
+just logs              # tail nginx access logs
+just ps                # docker compose ps
+just down              # stop nginx container (files preserved)
+just up                # bring it back (writes need sudo for _sync-caddy)
+sudo just _sync-caddy  # reload Caddy after editing caddy.snippet
+sudo just destroy      # nuke everything (asks for "yes" confirm)
+```
+
+## Tech stack
+
+- React 18 + Vite 6 + TypeScript strict (`noUnusedLocals: true`, `noUnusedParameters: true`)
+- Tailwind 4 — inline-style + CSS variables pattern, no utility classes
+- React Router v7 with `createBrowserRouter` (server **must** SPA-fallback to `index.html` — nginx.conf already does)
+- State: localStorage-backed stores with `listeners` Set + `useEffect`/`useState` hook pattern. The pipeline canon lives in `src/data/production-store.ts`.
+- Playwright smoke tests (no unit-test framework). Run `playwright test` directly.
+
+## What this app does NOT have
+
+- No backend service
+- No env vars at build or runtime
+- No CI auto-deploy — `npm run deploy` is the manual, intentional path
+- No multi-user data persistence — state is localStorage-only, per-browser
