+# Content Production Pipeline — Design Spec
+
+**Date:** 2026-05-22
+**Status:** Draft — pending user review
+**Brainstorm session:** restructuring-saas
+
+## Purpose
+
+Re-cast the existing `app/` (a multi-screen client-derived prototype) as a focused first SaaS: a **content production pipeline** that walks a solo creator from a raw idea through publishing a short-form vertical video. Replaces the heavier `saas/` direction.
+
+## Who it's for
+
+- **Primary user:** a solo short-form-video creator producing TikTok / Reels / YouTube Shorts.
+- **Secondary users:** occasional collaborators (editor, photographer, voice-over) the creator hands work off to. The creator runs the show.
+- **Out of scope for v1:** agencies, multi-creator managers, long-form video, newsletters, podcasts, photo-only posts, written threads, live streams.
+
+## Scope (v1)
+
+- One content format: short-form vertical video.
+- One workspace per creator (collaborators slot in later — see Deferred).
+- Pipeline operates on **Pieces** — one Piece = one specific video being made.
+- All collaborator handoff, platform-API integration, and metrics are deferred to v2.
+
+## Core concepts
+
+Three nouns. That's the whole model.
+
+### 1. Vault — raw idea backlog
+
+Holding tank for unstructured ideas. No stages, no deadlines, no statuses.
+
+Each Vault idea has:
+- **Title** (one line, optional)
+- **Content area** — pasted text from AI chats (long-form scrollable)
+- **References** — list of links + thumbnail screenshots
+- **Notes** — free-text scratchpad
+- **Tags** (optional, for grouping similar ideas — "fitness", "travel")
+- **Promote to Pipeline** button → creates a new Piece at Brainstorm stage
+
+Capture flow: click "+ New idea" → empty card → paste AI conversation, drop links, type a note → save. Comes back later, decides "yes, making this" → click Promote.
+
+What's explicitly NOT in the Vault: stages, collaborators, tasks, deadlines.
+
+### 2. Pipeline — 5-stage Kanban board
+
+Five columns, in order:
+
+1. **Brainstorm** — sharpen the rough idea
+2. **Pre-production** — plan the shoot
+3. **Production** — track the shoot
+4. **Post-production** — edit, polish, finalize per platform
+5. **Publish** — schedule + manually post
+
+Only Pieces the creator has committed to making live here.
+
+### 3. Piece — one specific video being made
+
+Has a current stage, structured content per stage, and a task list per stage. Lives on a card on the board; clicking opens its dedicated detail page.
+
+One Vault idea can spawn 0, 1, or many Pieces (creator clicks Promote repeatedly on the same Vault idea — each click creates a new Piece linked back to the Vault idea).
+
+## UI shape
+
+### Board overview (the Pipeline screen)
+
+```
+┌──────────┬──────────────┬────────────┬──────────────┬────────┐
+│Brainstorm│Pre-production│ Production │Post-production│Publish │
+├──────────┼──────────────┼────────────┼──────────────┼────────┤
+│ [Piece]  │   [Piece]    │            │   [Piece]    │[Piece] │
+│ [Piece]  │              │            │   [Piece]    │        │
+│ [Piece]  │              │            │              │        │
+└──────────┴──────────────┴────────────┴──────────────┴────────┘
+```
+
+Each card shows:
+- Title
+- Hook preview (first line, truncated)
+- Stage progress: `X of Y` checklist items done in current stage
+- Shoot date badge / scheduled publish badge, if any
+- Linked-from-Vault icon if it came from a Vault idea
+
+Interactions:
+- **Click card** → opens Piece detail
+- **Drag card** between columns → advances/retreats stage (warn on incomplete checklist; user can override)
+- **+ New Piece** on each column → creates a Piece directly at that stage (skipping Vault)
+
+No filters or sort in v1.
+
+### Piece detail page
+
+```
+< back to Pipeline                              [Advance →]
+
+Morning Routines #1                  Current stage: Pre-production
+Hook: "Stop opening your phone first thing —"
+Platforms: TikTok, Reels
+
+[ Brainstorm ✓ ] [ Pre-prod (4/7) ● ] [ Production ] [ Post ] [ Publish ]
+
+┌────────────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────┐
+│                                │                             │
+│      Structured content        │       Task list             │
+│      (script, shot list,       │       (suggested checklist  │
+│       captions, etc.)          │        + user-added tasks)  │
+│                                │                             │
+└────────────────────────────────┴─────────────────────────────┘
+```
+
+- Five **stage tabs** across the top, each showing completion status (`✓` done, `● X/Y` in progress, empty if not reached)
+- Clicking a tab navigates to that stage; user can revisit earlier stages at any time
+- **Advance →** button (top right) moves the Piece to the next stage. If the suggested checklist isn't complete, a warning modal lets the user override
+- **Left pane:** structured content blocks specific to the stage
+- **Right pane:** task list — pre-seeded suggested checklist + user-added tasks
+
+## Stage contents
+
+### Brainstorm (in-pipeline)
+
+*Purpose: sharpen the rough idea into something worth making.*
+
+Left pane:
+- **Source** — read-only window into the Vault idea this Piece came from (AI chat + references + notes). Editable if user adds more.
+- **Hook** — single-line, character-counted
+- **Platforms** — multi-select: TikTok / Reels / Shorts
+- **Angle / audience notes** — free text
+
+Suggested checklist:
+- [ ] Hook locked
+- [ ] Platforms picked
+
+### Pre-production
+
+*Purpose: plan the shoot. Flexible workspace — blocks pulled in as needed.*
+
+Left pane:
+- **Script / beat-by-beat outline** (rich text)
+- **Hook block** (carries from Brainstorm, editable)
+- **Shot list** (numbered list; each row: description + optional reference image)
+- **Storyboard** (gallery of uploaded sketches/references)
+- **Logistics** (location, props, wardrobe — checklist + free text)
+- **Shoot date** (date/time picker)
+- **Collaborator assignment** (name + role only in v1 — notifications deferred)
+- **References gallery** (links + screenshots)
+
+Suggested checklist:
+- [ ] Script written
+- [ ] Shot list ready
+- [ ] Shoot date set
+
+### Production
+
+*Purpose: track the shoot. No video storage — clips live in user's Drive / iCloud / etc.*
+
+Left pane:
+- **Shot list (live tick-off)** — same shot list from Pre-prod, now with checkboxes per shot
+- **Reshoot flags** — per shot, mark "needs reshoot" + reason
+- **Set notes** — free text
+- **Shoot done toggle** + date stamp
+
+Suggested checklist:
+- [ ] All shots captured (or reshoot-flagged)
+- [ ] Shoot marked done
+
+### Post-production
+
+*Purpose: edit, polish, finalize for each platform.*
+
+Left pane:
+- **Edit checklist** — sub-steps: rough cut → audio → color → captions/text-on-screen → music → final cut
+- **Final on-screen hook text** (the words shown over the first frame)
+- **Captions per platform** — separate text fields per selected platform (TikTok / Reels / Shorts)
+- **Hashtags / keywords**
+- **Music credits** (track name + link, for platform requirements)
+- **Collaborator review pane** — creator pastes external Frame.io / Drive / Vimeo link; comments thread (collaborator participation deferred to v2)
+
+Suggested checklist:
+- [ ] Cut final
+- [ ] Captions written per platform
+- [ ] Hashtags ready
+
+### Publish
+
+*Purpose: get it live, manually. No platform-API integration in v1.*
+
+Left pane:
+- **Per-platform schedule** — one row per platform selected back in Brainstorm. Each row: target date/time + "posted" toggle
+- **Reminders** — at the scheduled time, the tool sends an in-app reminder (optional email). User performs the actual posting on the platform
+- **Mark posted** — when the user ticks "posted" for a platform, the row stamps with the timestamp
+
+Suggested checklist:
+- [ ] Scheduled for each platform
+- [ ] Posted on each platform
+
+When all platform "posted" toggles are ticked, the Piece is **done**. Done Pieces stay in the Publish column with a `✓` marker. No archive view in v1.
+
+## Tasks
+
+Each stage's right pane is a task list with two sources:
+
+- **Suggested checklist** — pre-seeded items per stage (listed above). User can tick or untick.
+- **User-added tasks** — free-form additions ("buy props at IKEA", "ask Maria about Saturday"). Each task has a status (todo / doing / done) and (deferred) an assignee.
+
+A task is just a list item belonging to one stage of one Piece. No separate Tasks tab in the sidebar. No cross-Piece task aggregation in v1.
+
+## Advancement mechanic
+
+- **Advance →** button on Piece detail page (top right)
+- Drag-and-drop between columns on the board does the same thing
+- If the current stage's **suggested checklist** isn't fully ticked, a warning modal appears: *"3 items still unchecked — advance anyway?"*
+- User can always override and advance
+- User-added tasks do NOT block advancement (only suggested checklist items contribute to the advance gate)
+- Going backwards (dragging left, or clicking an earlier tab) is allowed and never warns
+
+## What this REPLACES from the existing app
+
+The current `app/` has 20+ screens from its client-project origin. This redesign trims aggressively.
+
+**Keep / repurpose:**
+- **Kanban screen** → becomes the Pipeline board
+- **Tasks screen** → folded into per-stage task panes on Piece detail
+- **Calendar screen** → could later show shoot dates + publish schedules (deferred)
+- **Login / Register / Settings** → unchanged (auth shell)
+- **Dashboard** → lighter version showing pipeline column counts
+
+**Cut for v1:**
+- Campaigns, Creators, Sponsors, Quotations, Invoices, Finance, Voting, Compliance, Inbox, Submit Idea, Sponsor Portal, Snapchat Entry, PDFReport — none fit the solo-creator content-pipeline use case.
+
+These can be revived later if a different SaaS direction emerges, but they don't ship in v1.
+
+## Deferred to v2
+
+- Collaborator notifications (magic-link vs. email vs. real accounts)
+- Auto-post via platform APIs (Meta Graph, TikTok API)
+- Auto-metrics from platform APIs
+- Manual metrics entry
+- "Archive" / "Published" filter view
+- Filters and sort on the board
+- Cross-Piece task aggregation (a "my tasks" view)
+- Calendar view of upcoming shoots and publishes
+- Multi-format support (long-form video, newsletters, podcasts, etc.)
+- Multi-creator / agency workspaces
+
+## Open questions (to resolve before implementation)
+
+1. **Storage budget for Vault attachments** — screenshots and reference images. Set per-workspace upload limit?
+2. **Reminder delivery channel for Publish stage** — in-app only, or also email? (Email needs a sender domain.)
+3. **Suggested checklist mutability** — can users edit the suggested checklist items themselves, or are they fixed in code per stage? (v1 recommendation: fixed in code; promote to settings later.)
+4. **Re-running a Piece** — if a creator wants to make a v2 of a published Piece, do they duplicate it back into Brainstorm, or is that a new Piece linked to the old? (v1 recommendation: duplicate to new Piece, link via "based on" field.)
+
+## Out of scope (intentionally not included)
+
+- Long-form video, newsletter, podcast, photo, written-thread, live-stream pipelines
+- Multi-creator / team / agency views
+- Built-in AI chat (users paste from external AI tools)
+- Video file storage / transcoding
+- Platform API publishing or analytics
+- Billing / payments / subscription management
+- Sponsor / advertiser flows
+- Compliance / approval flows
