+# Workspace Jurisdiction — Design
+
+**Date:** 2026-05-23
+**Status:** Approved (brainstorm) → ready for implementation plan
+**Branch:** `fix/devpanel-bool-gate` (stacked on `restructuring-saas-design`)
+
+## Problem
+
+The ZATCA (Saudi FATOORA e-invoicing) settings tab is hardcoded English and
+gated only by role (`MANAGE_USERS`). Two issues surface from this:
+
+1. ZATCA content should be presented in Arabic for Saudi operators, but the
+   tab is not wired into the app's existing AR/EN i18n at all.
+2. More fundamentally, ZATCA visibility is tied to *role*, not to *whether the
+   workspace operates in Saudi Arabia*. There is no concept of a workspace's
+   operating country, so country-specific compliance features cannot be scoped
+   — and the product intends to expand to other countries.
+
+The fix is not to pin the ZATCA tab to Arabic. It is to introduce a
+**jurisdiction** concept that scopes country-specific features and defaults,
+and to make ZATCA properly translatable so it honors the operator's language
+preference (Arabic by default for Saudi workspaces, English on request).
+
+## Core model: two orthogonal axes
+
+Language and jurisdiction are independent and must never be inferred from each
+other. A user who prefers an English UI can operate a workspace based in KSA —
+ZATCA still applies, invoice output is still Arabic-mandated, but that operator
+reads English labels.
+
+| Axis | Lives on | Drives | Set by |
+|---|---|---|---|
+| **Language** (`en` / `ar`) | per-user (`prefs.language`, exists today) | UI text + RTL direction | the user, freely, anytime |
+| **Jurisdiction** (`SA` / `INTL`) | per-workspace (`Workspace.jurisdiction`, new) | which compliance features exist; default currency, VAT rate, tax-ID label; *suggested* initial language | workspace owner, **at onboarding only — immutable thereafter** |
+
+**Hard rule:** jurisdiction never writes `prefs.language` at render time. Its
+`suggestedLanguage` seeds the *initial* UI language exactly once, at first
+workspace creation, and only if the user has not already chosen one. After that,
+the user's toggle always wins.
+
+**Immutability:** jurisdiction mirrors the existing `AccountWorkspace.role`
+pattern ("IMMUTABLE once set"). It is chosen at onboarding and never editable
+afterward; to change it you recreate the workspace. The only exception is the
+one-time migration backfill for workspaces that predate the field.
+
+## Section 1 — Data model
+
+New registry module `src/data/jurisdictions.ts`:
+
+```ts
+type Jurisdiction = 'SA' | 'INTL';   // extensible: add 'GB' | 'AE' | 'US' later
+
+interface JurisdictionConfig {
+  code: Jurisdiction;
+  label: { en: string; ar: string };
+  defaultCurrency: 'SAR' | 'USD' | 'EUR';
+  defaultVatRate: number;                  // SA: 0.15, INTL: 0
+  suggestedLanguage: LangKey;              // SA: 'ar', INTL: 'en' — a hint, never a lock
+  taxIdLabel: { en: string; ar: string };  // "VAT number" / "الرقم الضريبي"
+  features: { zatca: boolean };            // SA: true, INTL: false
+}
+
+const JURISDICTIONS: Record<Jurisdiction, JurisdictionConfig> = { SA: {…}, INTL: {…} };
+```
+
+Changes to `Workspace` (`src/types/saas.ts`):
+- **Add** `jurisdiction: Jurisdiction` (authoritative, immutable after creation).
+- `currency`, `vatRate` stay optional and become **derived-with-override**: when
+  absent, resolve to the jurisdiction default. A free-zone exception can still
+  override explicitly.
+- Legacy free-text `country` and `locale` are **removed** from the `Workspace`
+  type. They are read once during migration to infer `jurisdiction`, then
+  deleted from stored records and the type. Any remaining readers are updated to
+  use `jurisdiction` / `jurisdictionOf(ws)`.
+
+## Section 2 — Feature-gating & data flow
+
+Helpers (in `jurisdictions.ts`):
+```ts
+jurisdictionOf(ws): JurisdictionConfig    // ws.jurisdiction → registry entry (fallback INTL)
+hasFeature(ws, 'zatca'): boolean          // = jurisdictionOf(ws).features.zatca
+```
+
+ZATCA tab gating changes from role-only to **role AND jurisdiction**:
+```
+ZATCA tab visible  ⇔  canManageUsers && hasFeature(currentWs, 'zatca')
+```
+ZATCA shows only to Admins of SA workspaces. Every future compliance module
+gates the same way on its own `features.*` flag — no new gating machinery.
+
+Snap-back: jurisdiction is immutable, so it does NOT need to be added to the
+Settings.tsx snap-back effect deps. Only role changes (the Dev tools role
+switcher) drive snap-back, which is already handled.
+
+Currency & VAT data flow (workspace-sourced, never user-preference):
+- Money formatting and the invoice generator read
+  `currency = ws.currency ?? jurisdictionOf(ws).defaultCurrency` and
+  `vatRate = ws.vatRate ?? jurisdictionOf(ws).defaultVatRate`.
+- `invoice-store.ts` stops hardcoding `currencyID="SAR"` and uses the resolved
+  workspace currency. (For SA it remains SAR — no visible change today.)
+- Tax-ID field label reads `jurisdictionOf(ws).taxIdLabel[lang]`.
+
+UI text language and RTL continue to flow purely from `prefs.language`.
+Jurisdiction never touches them at render time.
+
+## Section 3 — Settings UI & i18n wiring
+
+- **Jurisdiction picker lives in Onboarding** as a required step in workspace
+  creation. On first run it seeds `prefs.language` from `suggestedLanguage` only
+  if the user has not chosen a language yet.
+- **`WorkspaceSection` shows jurisdiction read-only** (a labeled display row),
+  visible to Admins but not editable. Currency stays editable (override case).
+- **ZATCA section wired into AR/EN i18n** (`src/lib/i18n/settings.ts`): all
+  hardcoded English (headings, OTP field labels, helper text, warning banners,
+  buttons) moves to `settings.zatca.*` keys with `en` + `ar` values, read via
+  `t(key, lang)`.
+  - Provider brand names (Wafeq, HAL VATCare, ClearTax) stay literal; their
+    descriptive `sub` lines are translated.
+- Effect: an SA Admin sees the ZATCA tab in Arabic by default (seeded language),
+  but the tab follows the user's toggle if they prefer English.
+
+## Section 4 — Migration & build slice
+
+**Migration** (`saas-migration.ts`, one-time, the sole immutability exception):
+backfill `jurisdiction` for existing workspaces by inferring from existing
+signals — Saudi `country` / `locale` starting `*-SA` / `currency === 'SAR'` /
+presence of a `vatNumber` → `SA`; otherwise `INTL`. The legacy `country` and
+`locale` values are deleted from each record in the same pass. After backfill
+the `jurisdiction` field is frozen.
+
+**Build slice (implement now, YAGNI):**
+1. `jurisdictions.ts` registry with only `SA` + `INTL`.
+2. `Workspace.jurisdiction` field + `jurisdictionOf` / `hasFeature` helpers.
+3. Migration backfill.
+4. Onboarding: required jurisdiction step; seeds `suggestedLanguage` on first run only.
+5. `WorkspaceSection`: read-only jurisdiction row; currency/VAT resolve via jurisdiction defaults.
+6. Settings: ZATCA tab gates on `canManageUsers && hasFeature(ws,'zatca')`.
+7. ZATCA section + tax-ID label wired into AR/EN i18n.
+8. `invoice-store.ts`: resolved currency instead of hardcoded `SAR`.
+
+**Deferred:** additional jurisdictions (GB/US/AE/India), per-jurisdiction
+invoice formats beyond ZATCA, any jurisdiction-change flow (recreate-only by
+design).
+
+## Test strategy
+
+Playwright smoke (the project's only test framework):
+- SA workspace shows the ZATCA tab; INTL workspace does not.
+- ZATCA tab renders Arabic when `lang=ar`, English when `lang=en`.
+- Jurisdiction is read-only in `WorkspaceSection`.
+- Migration assigns `SA` to a workspace with `currency==='SAR'` / a `vatNumber`.
+- Onboarding requires a jurisdiction selection and seeds language on first run.
+
+## Resolved decisions
+
+- **Legacy fields:** `country` / `locale` are removed from `Workspace` after the
+  migration reads them (see Section 4).
+- **Arabic translations:** drafted below (Appendix A). These are Modern Standard
+  Arabic drafts; a native KSA tax-domain reviewer should still verify the
+  compliance terminology before production, but they are complete and usable as-is.
+
